<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=747&amp;p=6481#p6481"><![CDATA[
Apologies if this has been suggested before, but I just thought of something.  Would it be possible to make a NES cartridge that has, say, a secure digital flash memory slot in it, that lets you put ROM files on the flash card, put the flash card into the cartridge, put the cartridge/adapter into a regular NES and play the games as if it were a regular cartridge?  Maybe it would include a custom multi-game menu on a rom that automatically starts up and lets you select the game you want to play.  Also, it could save SRAM data to the flash card.<br /><br />I'd pay some real money for that.  I guess the trick would be containing the whole design in a package the size of a NES cartridge.  Maybe Kevtris could tackle it? <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />RedWolf<br /><br />---<br /><a href="http://www.vintagecomputing.com" class="postlink">Vintage Computing and Gaming</a><p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Fri Nov 11, 2005 10:34 pm</p><hr />
